The National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) Yobe State has held its second-quarter 2022 Health Initiative for Rural Dwellers at Garin Daye Community in Potiskum LGA of the state. The turnout for the programme was huge, before the arrival of the medical team from the NYSC, the venue was already filled to the brim. Flagging off the programme the Yobe State NYSC Coordinator Mrs Hafsat Yerima stated that the programme was designed to take health care service delivery to the doorsteps of the rural people. The Coordinator further stated that a total of 2000 to 3000 indigent people are expected to benefit from the programme. Continuing, Mrs Yerima said that the scheme in collaboration with its partners will continue to deploy the expertise of its Corps Manpower in the area of health care service to better a lot of its host communities. She applauded the community for coming out en-mass to participate in the programme. In a goodwill message delivered on his behalf by Director Primary Health Care of the Ministry Mal. Musa Yelwa, the Commissioner of Health Yobe State thanked the NYSC for this laudable effort. He further stated that the Ministry will continue to work with the scheme to enhance the health well being of the people. Also contributing the Coordinator United Nations Fund for Population Activities (UNFPA) Yobe State Mal. (Dr) Awal Bashir applauded the scheme for its giant stride in improving the health care needs of the people. He assured of the continued support of the Fund for the sustenance of the programme. The Coordinator donated womenâ€™s delivery kits to support the initiative. Corps Personnel comprising Doctors, Pharmacist, Nurses Lab Scientists etc were deployed for the programme.